Kevin Pietersen  has been left out
of defending champion  England 's squad for the ICC World Twenty20 
competition in  Sri Lanka  next month.  He’s also omitted from England’s squad for the one-day and
Twenty20 matches against  South Africa  starting Aug. 24.  Pietersen missed the third Test against South Africa after
sending “provocative”  text messages  to members of the opposing
team, and had also been involved in a wrangle with the England
and Wales Cricket Board over his playing commitments.  The board announced the following squads:  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
